# User Story Format

When working with any file that has 'story', 'user story', or 'feature' in the filename, format the document according to the following guidelines:

## Story Title
- Start with a descriptive title
- Use a consistent ID or reference number
- Include story priority or MoSCoW rating

## User Story Format
- As a [role]
- I want to [capability]
- So that [benefit/value]

## Acceptance Criteria
- Use the Given/When/Then format
- Be specific and testable
- Cover happy paths and edge cases

## Additional Information
- Include technical notes if applicable
- Add UI/UX mockups or references
- Document dependencies on other stories

## Estimation
- Story points or time estimate
- Complexity rating
- Risk factors

## Implementation Notes
- Technical approach considerations
- Potential challenges
- Testing strategies